  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>cglame</command>

      <arg><replaceable>swapfile</replaceable></arg>

    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>This manual page documents briefly the
      <command>cglame</command> command.</para>

    <para>This manual page was written for the &debian; distribution
      because the original program does not have a manual page.
      Instead, it has documentation in the &gnu;
      <application>Info</application> format; see below.</para>

    <para><command>cglame</command> is a program that provides you with
	a flexible command line interface to edit and manipulate audio
	streams. It uses a scripting language built on top of Scheme that
	is described in the <application>Info</application> manual.</para>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>swapfile
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>File that acts as cglame's backing store. If you do not
		specify a swapfile, editing capabilities are limited by
		available memory.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>SEE ALSO</title>

    <para>The programs are documented fully by <citetitle>The GLAME
      Manual</citetitle> available via the
      <application>Info</application> system.</para>
